Sentencas: Samarium-doped ceria (SDC) nanowires are synthesized by a novel, template-, surfactant-free and cost-effective method, using citric acid as precipitating/complexing agent for formation of citrate precursor nanowires.
Titulo: Samarium-Doped Ceria Nanowires: Novel Synthesis and Application in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The single SOFC based on SDC nanowires/Na2CO3 nanocomposites as electrolyte is fabricated and the maximum power densities of 417 and 522 mW cm(-2) at 550 and 600 degrees C are achieved, showing great potential for low-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Samarium-Doped Ceria Nanowires: Novel Synthesis and Application in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
